  "chapter": {
    "number": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Out of Egypt I Called My Son"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When Israel was a child, I loved him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and out of Egypt I called My son.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2494
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the more I called Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the farther they departed from Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2495
          },
          {
            "text": "They sacrificed to the Baals",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and burned incense to carved images.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It was I who taught Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2496
          },
          {
            "text": "to walk,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "taking them in My arms,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but they never realized",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that it was I who healed them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I led them with cords of kindness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with ropes of love;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I lifted the yoke from their necks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bent down to feed them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will they not return to the land of Egypt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and be ruled by Assyria",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they refused to repent?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A sword will flash through their cities;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will destroy the bars of their gates",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and consume them in their own plans.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My people are bent on turning from Me.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Though they call to the Most High,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will by no means exalt them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Love for Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How could I give you up, O Ephraim?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "How could I surrender you, O Israel?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "How could I make you like Admah?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "How could I treat you like Zeboiim?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My heart is turned within Me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My compassion is stirred!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will not execute the full fury of My anger;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not turn back to destroy Ephraim.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For I am God and not man—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One among you—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will not come in wrath.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will walk after the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will roar like a lion.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When He roars,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His children will come trembling from the west.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will come trembling like birds from Egypt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and like doves from the land of Assyria.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then I will settle them in their homes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim surrounds Me with lies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the house of Israel with deceit;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but Judah still walks with God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and is faithful to the Holy One.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2497
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
